    "content": "🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"**/running-agents*.{ts,tsx}\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"**/use-running-agents*.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"runningAgents|running.*agents\",\n  \"glob\": \"*.{ts,tsx}\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\use-running-agents.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\running-agents-indicator.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\running-agents\\\\routes\\\\index.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\board-view\\\\components\\\\running-agents-panel.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"runningAgentsData|setRunningAgents|RunningAgents\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 1,\n  \"limit\": 200\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 910,\n  \"limit\": 50\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 1700,\n  \"limit\": 80\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\board-view.tsx\",\n  \"offset\": 1,\n  \"limit\": 100\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"useRunningAgents|running.*agents\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\board-view.tsx\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"useRunningAgentsPolling\",\n  \"glob\": \"*.{ts,tsx}\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"RunningAgentsIndicator\",\n  \"glob\": \"*.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\top-nav-bar.tsx\",\n  \"offset\": 1,\n  \"limit\": 150\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"TopNavigationBar\",\n  \"glob\": \"*.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\__root.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"useRunningAgents\\\\b(?!Polling)\",\n  \"glob\": \"*.{ts,tsx}\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"from.*use-running-agents|useRunningAgents\\\\(\",\n  \"glob\": \"*.{ts,tsx}\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\dylan\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\index.ts\"\n}\nNow I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me generate the comprehensive specification.\n\n---\n\n# Specification: Independent Running Agents Polling\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\nThe Running Agents indicator in the top navigation bar does not update in real-time until the user changes the board project. Currently, although the `useRunningAgentsPolling` hook is designed to poll every 30 seconds independently of board state, the UI updates are not reflecting agent status changes until a project switch triggers component re-renders. The running agents display should update continuously regardless of user interactions with the board.\n\n## 2. User Story\nAs a **user with multiple projects running agents**, I want **the running agents indicator to update automatically every 30 seconds across all projects**, so that **I can monitor agent status in real-time without needing to manually refresh or switch projects**.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Happy Path\n- **GIVEN** the application is loaded with running agents across multiple projects, **WHEN** 30 seconds pass, **THEN** the running agents count and list update automatically without user interaction\n- **GIVEN** an agent completes or starts in a background project, **WHEN** the next polling cycle occurs, **THEN** the running agents indicator reflects the change\n- **GIVEN** the user is on project A, **WHEN** project B's agent status changes, **THEN** the indicator shows the updated count for all projects\n\n### Edge Cases  \n- **GIVEN** no running agents, **WHEN** a new agent starts in any project, **THEN** the indicator updates from 0 to 1 within 30 seconds\n- **GIVEN** the polling hook is mounted in multiple components, **WHEN** both poll simultaneously, **THEN** only one fetch occurs (deduplicated)\n- **GIVEN** the user navigates between views, **WHEN** the view changes, **THEN** polling continues uninterrupted\n\n### Error Handling\n- **GIVEN** the server is temporarily unavailable, **WHEN** a poll fails, **THEN** the last known agent data is retained and error state is set\n- **GIVEN** a network timeout occurs, **WHEN** the next poll succeeds, **THEN** the indicator updates with fresh data\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files | `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts`, `apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts`, `apps/ui/src/components/layout/running-agents-indicator.tsx` |\n| Dependencies | Zustand (state management), React hooks |\n| Constraints | Must maintain backward compatibility with existing polling behavior |\n| Patterns to Follow | Zustand subscription pattern with stable selectors, singleton polling pattern |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n- Real-time WebSocket push notifications (out of scope - polling-based approach is acceptable)\n- Changing the 30-second polling interval default\n- Modifying server-side running agents endpoints\n- Adding new API endpoints\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: Foundation - Create Singleton Polling Manager\n- [ ] T001: Create singleton polling manager class in use-running-agents.ts | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n- [ ] T002: Implement reference counting for polling subscriptions | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n- [ ] T003: Add automatic start/stop based on subscriber count | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n\n## Phase 2: Core Implementation - Store and Hook Updates  \n- [ ] T004: Ensure store updates trigger Zustand subscription notifications | File: apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts\n- [ ] T005: Refactor useRunningAgentsPolling to use singleton manager | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n- [ ] T006: Add debug logging to track polling lifecycle events | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n\n## Phase 3: Integration & Verification\n- [ ] T007: Update RunningAgentsIndicator to use refactored hook | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/running-agents-indicator.tsx\n- [ ] T008: Verify polling continues during project switches | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n- [ ] T009: Add manual polling trigger for immediate refresh | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n- Running agents count updates every 30 seconds without user interaction (verifiable via debug logs)\n- Project switch does not interrupt or reset the polling interval\n- UI reflects agent status changes within one polling cycle (30 seconds max)\n- Single polling instance runs regardless of how many components subscribe\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Singleton manager may not be garbage collected | Use reference counting with automatic cleanup when subscriber count reaches 0 |\n| Multiple rapid mounts/unmounts could cause race conditions | Debounce start/stop logic with a short delay |\n| Store updates not triggering re-renders | Ensure immutable state updates and verify selector equality checks |\n\n---",
